10 Subject: Regulated drugs; unlawful drug activity in a dwelling; flash citation
11 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to require that in
12 cases when a person is arraigned on a charge of unlawful drug activity in a
13 dwelling where the person is not a legal tenant, the State’s Attorney shall
14 request as a condition of release that the person is prohibited from coming
15 within a fixed distance of the dwelling.
16 An act relating to unlawful drug activity in a dwelling by a person who is
17 not a legal tenant
18 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
19 Sec. 1. 18 V.S.A. § 4252a is amended to read:
20 § 4252a. UNLAWFUL DRUG ACTIVITY IN A DWELLING; FLASH
VT LEG #379852 v.1

