1 CITATION
2 (a) Except for good cause shown, a person cited or arrested for dispensing
3 or selling a regulated drug in violation of this chapter shall be arraigned on the
4 next business day after the citation or arrest if the alleged illegal activity
5 occurred at a dwelling where the person is not a legal tenant.
6 (b) Unless the person is held without bail for another offense, the State’s
7 Attorney may shall request conditions of release. The court may include as a
8 condition of release that the person is prohibited from coming within a fixed
9 distance of the dwelling.
10 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
11 This act shall take effect on July 1, 2025.
